    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it doesn't feel like a state that can change. it feels like a fundamental truth. if the pilot is gone, the plane is just falling. it's just metal and weight and nothingness. why should the machine keep running if there's nobody at the controls anymore? it just seems so illogical to keep going when the core of me is already extinct.",
